<p>
<font size=5>About me</font>
<hr/>
I am a post doc in the Dept of ORFE, Princeton University.  I am broadly interested in probability theory and its applications. In particular, I have been working on determinantal point process, rigidity phenomena in point sets, random polynomials and random analytic functions. My mentor at Princeton is <a target="_blank" href="http://www.princeton.edu/~rvan/">Prof. Ramon van Handel</a>. Before this, I obtained my PhD in Mathematics at the University of California, Berkeley, in May 2013 under the supervision of <a  target="_blank" href="http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/um/people/peres/">Prof. Yuval Peres</a>. Earlier, I obtained my Bachelor in Statistics and Master in Mathematics degrees at the Indian Statistical Institute.
</p>

<p>
